<body>
<h1> AI Entry Approval Gate</h1>
<p class="meta"><strong>OraBooks Lean MVP</strong> - Complete Implementation Report<br>Generated: June 2026</p>

<h2>1. Executive Summary</h2>
<p> implements the human journal approval workflow. AI never approves entries; it only provides confidence scores via /. This report documents completion of all Phase 0-4 gaps.</p>

<h2>2. Core Guarantees Delivered</h2>
<ul>
<li>Only approver/owner (or active delegate) can approve or reject journals.</li>
<li>Append-only journal_approval_history with MySQL triggers blocking UPDATE/DELETE.</li>
<li>No rejected status - reject returns journal to draft with immutable history record.</li>
<li>revision_number tracks content edits; approval_round tracks submit/resubmit cycles.</li>
<li>Snapshot hash on submit (history) and approve (approved_snapshot_hash).</li>
<li>Posting requires status=approved and approval_stale=false.</li>
<li>MFA for high-value approvals; maker-checker policy enforced.</li>
<li>Escalation and expiry crons with idempotency guards.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Backend Changes</h2>
<ul>
<li>promote_to_review_pending clears approved_snapshot_hash on submit.</li>
<li>Escalation cron skips duplicate escalate per approval_round.</li>
<li>Expiry reminder cron uses transient to prevent duplicate reminders.</li>
<li>Delegation create publishes approval_delegated outbox event.</li>
<li>Expiry publishes approval_expired and journal_approval_expired.</li>
<li>Invoice post submits journal into review_pending queue.</li>
<li>Deploy checks include tables and approval crons.</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. UI Deliverables</h2>
<ul>
<li>JournalsPage: Approval History tab, resubmit, MFA/reject modals, accent styling.</li>
<li>ApprovalsPage: Sort dropdown, styled modals, settings link.</li>
<li>Approval Settings: policy CRUD and delegation (owner only).</li>
<li>UI accent color matches sidebar active menu (bg-accent).</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Test Coverage</h2>
<p><strong>OraBooks_Approval_Test.php</strong> - 17 tests, all passing.</p>

<h2>6. How to Test (Manual)</h2>
<ol>
<li>Login as creator: create draft journal, submit for approval.</li>
<li>Login as approver: Approvals page, sort queue, approve (MFA if high value).</li>
<li>Post approved journal; check Reports/Trial Balance.</li>
<li>Reject with reason; verify Draft (Rejected) and resubmit.</li>
<li>Owner: Approval Settings - policy and delegation.</li>
<li>Post invoice; verify journal in Approvals queue.</li>
</ol>

<h2>7. How to Test (Automated)</h2>
<p><code>php tests/vendor/bin/phpunit --configuration tests/phpunit.xml tests/OraBooks_Approval_Test.php</code></p>

<h2>8. Status</h2>
<p class="status"><strong> Lean MVP: COMPLETE</strong> - all checklist gaps addressed.</p>
</body>
</html>
